hotos/5b646c1d7e2a9576a88d599e/16:9/w_1280,c_limit/portland-maine-the-shop-2.jpg 1x, https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b646c1d7e2a9576a88d599e/16:9/w_2560,c_limit/portland-maine-the-shop-2.jpg 2x" media="(min-width: 1280px)" data-reactid="121"/><source srcset="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b646c1d7e2a9576a88d599e/16:9/w_1028,c_limit/portland-maine-the-shop-2.jpg 1x, https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b646c1d7e2a9576a88d599e/16:9/w_2056,c_limit/portland-maine-the-shop-2.jpg 2x" media="(min-width: 1024px)" data-reactid="122"/><source srcset="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b646c1d7e2a9576a88d599e/1:1/w_768,h_768,c_limit/portland-maine-the-shop-2.jpg 1x, https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b646c1d7e2a9576a88d599e/1:1/w_1536,h_1536,c_limit/portland-maine-the-shop-2.jpg 2x" media="(min-width: 768px)" data-reactid="123"/><source srcset="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b646c1d7e2a9576a88d599e/1:1/w_414,h_414,c_limit/portland-maine-the-shop-2.jpg 1x, https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b646c1d7e2a9576a88d599e/1:1/w_828,h_828,c_limit/portland-maine-the-shop-2.jpg 2x" media="(min-width: 0px)" data-reactid="124"/><img class="ba-picture--fit" srcset="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b646c1d7e2a9576a88d599e/16:9/w_940,c_limit/portland-maine-the-shop-2.jpg 1x, https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b646c1d7e2a9576a88d599e/16:9/w_1880,c_limit/portland-maine-the-shop-2.jpg 2x" alt="portland-maine-the-shop-2.jpg" data-reactid="125"/></picture></div><figcaption class="toutimagenarrow-credit" data-reactid="126"><cite class="credit  align-to-container" data-reactid="127">Greta Rybus</cite></figcaption></figure><!-- react-empty: 128 --><div class="grid grid--post-layout" data-component="Grid" data-reactid="129"><div data-reactid="130"><div class="row row--MainWithSidebar" data-component="Row" data-reactid="131"><div class="col col-xs-4 col-sm-10 col-md-8 col--MainWithSidebar col--main-content" data-component="Col" data-reactid="132"><div class="content-group" data-reactid="133"><p data-reactid="134"><strong data-reactid="135">Full disclosure: I’ve got a thing for Maine.</strong><!-- react-text: 136 --> I went to college there, I got married there, I regularly vacation there. And I’ve always believed that Portland has one of the more vibrant, compelling food scenes, thanks in no small part to all that pristine seafood and craft beer. I’ve written about the Forest City (who knew it was called that?) and its restaurants more than any other city besides New York. I even called it <!-- /react-text --><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234/https://www.bonappetit.com/columns/the-foodist/article/portland-maine-america-s-foodiest-small-town-2009" data-reactid="137">America’s Foodiest Small Town</a><!-- react-text: 138 --> in a 2009 story (wow, that title didn’t age well). So, why should you believe me when I declare Portland our 2018 City of the Year? And after years of me talking about it, why now?<!-- /react-text --></p><p data-reactid="139">For starters, it’s the sheer number of outstanding openings—from a tiny pastry shop that serves knockout Roman pizza to a Jewish-style deli that ranks up there with New York and L.A.’s best. And while you can still get an Instagram-worthy lobster roll and a dozen local oysters, you’re missing out if you skip the killer pho spot or the guy selling hand rolls out of a Yeti cooler.</p><p data-reactid="140">No, this year’s award isn’t a case blind favoritism. It’s simply because this always-tasty city has never tasted better. Want more proof? Here are 20 ways to binge your way through it right now.</p><ol data-reactid="141"><li data-reactid="142"><p data-reactid="143"><!-- react-text: 144 -->Start every day with a trip to <!-- /react-text --><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234/https://www.tandemcoffee.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-reactid="145">Tandem Bakery</a><!-- react-text: 146 -->. I find it almost impossible to order anything other than a biscuit slathered in butter and blueberry jam. Wait, I mean the sticky bun. No, the black sesame and banana tea cake. Then again, pretty much everything baker Briana Holt whips up is brilliant.<!-- /react-text --></p></li><li data-reactid="147"><p data-reactid="148"><!-- react-text: 149 -->Get a glass of on-tap Maine-made pét-nat <!-- /react-text --><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234/http://www.oysterriverwine.com/wines/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-reactid="150">Morphos</a><!-- react-text: 151 -->, throw back expertly shucked oysters and baby scallops (when in season), and you could easily spend your entire afternoon at <!-- /react-text --><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234/http://portland.islandcreekoysters.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-reactid="152">The Shop at Island Creek Oysters</a><!-- react-text: 153 -->.<!-- /react-text --></p></li><li data-reactid="154"><p data-reactid="155"><!-- react-text: 156 -->Treat the high-energy <!-- /react-text --><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234/http://www.izakayaminato.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-reactid="157">Izakaya Minato</a><!-- react-text: 158 --> like a sushi bar: Sit at the low-slung kitchen counter and ask chef-owner Thomas Takashi Cooke to give you whatever was swimming nearby yesterday (mackerel, uni, scallops). And when you’ve polished that off, order another glass of sake and a couple plates of JFC (Japanese fried chicken).<!-- /react-text --></p></li></ol><figure class="embedded-image embedded-image--no-callout" data-type="image" data-reactid="159"><div class="image-content" data-reactid="160"><div class="component-rendition ba-picture size_w414 size_h0 sm_w768 sm_h0 md_w1024 md_h0 lg_w1440 lg_h0 xl_w2000 xl_h0 xs_w414 xs_h0" data-component="Rendition" style="background-image:url(https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64670ef0db7b6ba2310783/master/w_10,c_limit/Portland-Maine-the-shop.jpg);background-size:cover;background-repeat:no-repeat;" data-reactid="161"><picture data-reactid="162"><source srcset="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64670ef0db7b6ba2310783/master/w_2000/Portland-Maine-the-shop.jpg 1x, https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64670ef0db7b6ba2310783/master/w_4000/Portland-Maine-the-shop.jpg 2x" media="(min-width: 1488px)" data-reactid="163"/><source srcset="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64670ef0db7b6ba2310783/master/w_1440/Portland-Maine-the-shop.jpg 1x, https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64670ef0db7b6ba2310783/master/w_2880/Portland-Maine-the-shop.jpg 2x" media="(min-width: 1280px)" data-reactid="164"/><source srcset="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64670ef0db7b6ba2310783/master/w_1024/Portland-Maine-the-shop.jpg 1x, https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64670ef0db7b6ba2310783/master/w_2048/Portland-Maine-the-shop.jpg 2x" media="(min-width: 1024px)" data-reactid="165"/><source srcset="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64670ef0db7b6ba2310783/master/w_768/Portland-Maine-the-shop.jpg 1x, https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64670ef0db7b6ba2310783/master/w_1536/Portland-Maine-the-shop.jpg 2x" media="(min-width: 768px)" data-reactid="166"/><source srcset="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64670ef0db7b6ba2310783/master/w_414,c_limit/Portland-Maine-the-shop.jpg 1x, https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64670ef0db7b6ba2310783/master/w_828,c_limit/Portland-Maine-the-shop.jpg 2x" media="(min-width: 0px)" data-reactid="167"/><img class="ba-picture--fit" srcset="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64670ef0db7b6ba2310783/master/w_414,c_limit/Portland-Maine-the-shop.jpg 1x, https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64670ef0db7b6ba2310783/master/w_828,c_limit/Portland-Maine-the-shop.jpg 2x" alt="Portland Maine the shop" data-reactid="168"/></picture></div></div><figcaption class="callout-image-caption clearfix" data-reactid="169"><div class="credits" data-reactid="170">Greta Rybus</div><span class="caption" data-reactid="171"><p>Oysters, pét-nat, repeat at The Shop at Island Creek Oysters</p>
</span></figcaption></figure><ol start="4" data-reactid="172"><li data-reactid="173"><p data-reactid="174"><!-- react-text: 175 -->Stay at the 15-room <!-- /react-text --><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234/https://thefrancismaine.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-reactid="176">Francis Hotel</a><!-- react-text: 177 --> set in a historic Victorian Mansion (I prefer the junior suite, room 303). At night I like to sip an old-fashioned in front of the fireplace, but the best reason to stay here might be the fact that it’s located directly across the street from Tandem Bakery (see No. 1).<!-- /react-text --></p></li><li data-reactid="178"><p data-reactid="179"><!-- react-text: 180 -->Forget trendy and head to <!-- /react-text --><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234/https://www.facebook.com/pages/Ruskis-Tavern/115551755131665" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-reactid="181">Ruski’s Tavern</a><!-- react-text: 182 -->, a neighborhood bar that is open from 7 a.m. (9 a.m. on Sundays) and serves just about every bar food you can imagine. The chili cheese dog will not disappoint. If this place ever dies, so too will Portland.<!-- /react-text --></p></li><li data-reactid="183"><p data-reactid="184"><!-- react-text: 185 -->Hit up the Jewish deli that’s worth its weight in legit bagels: <!-- /react-text --><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234/https://www.rosefoods.me/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-reactid="186">Rose Foods</a><!-- react-text: 187 -->. Yes, I just said that (it&#x27;s on our <!-- /react-text --><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234/https://www.bonappetit.com/story/top-50-best-new-restaurants-2018" data-reactid="188">Top 50</a><!-- react-text: 189 --> list!). And after you’ve loaded up on perfect Montreal-style bagels, crispy latkes, and a big bowl of matzo ball soup, be sure to purchase one of their soon-to-be-famous canvas totes.<!-- /react-text --></p></li></ol><figure class="embedded-image embedded-image--no-callout" data-type="image" data-reactid="190"><div class="image-content" data-reactid="191"><div class="component-rendition ba-picture size_w414 size_h0 sm_w768 sm_h0 md_w1024 md_h0 lg_w1440 lg_h0 xl_w2000 xl_h0 xs_w414 xs_h0" data-component="Rendition" style="background-image:url(https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64776ef0db7b6ba2310785/master/w_10,c_limit/Portland-Maine-rose-1.jpg);background-size:cover;background-repeat:no-repeat;" data-reactid="192"><picture data-reactid="193"><source srcset="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64776ef0db7b6ba2310785/master/w_2000/Portland-Maine-rose-1.jpg 1x, https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64776ef0db7b6ba2310785/master/w_4000/Portland-Maine-rose-1.jpg 2x" media="(min-width: 1488px)" data-reactid="194"/><source srcset="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64776ef0db7b6ba2310785/master/w_1440/Portland-Maine-rose-1.jpg 1x, https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64776ef0db7b6ba2310785/master/w_2880/Portland-Maine-rose-1.jpg 2x" media="(min-width: 1280px)" data-reactid="195"/><source srcset="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64776ef0db7b6ba2310785/master/w_1024/Portland-Maine-rose-1.jpg 1x, https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64776ef0db7b6ba2310785/master/w_2048/Portland-Maine-rose-1.jpg 2x" media="(min-width: 1024px)" data-reactid="196"/><source srcset="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64776ef0db7b6ba2310785/master/w_768/Portland-Maine-rose-1.jpg 1x, https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64776ef0db7b6ba2310785/master/w_1536/Portland-Maine-rose-1.jpg 2x" media="(min-width: 768px)" data-reactid="197"/><source srcset="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64776ef0db7b6ba2310785/master/w_414,c_limit/Portland-Maine-rose-1.jpg 1x, https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64776ef0db7b6ba2310785/master/w_828,c_limit/Portland-Maine-rose-1.jpg 2x" media="(min-width: 0px)" data-reactid="198"/><img class="ba-picture--fit" srcset="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64776ef0db7b6ba2310785/master/w_414,c_limit/Portland-Maine-rose-1.jpg 1x, https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64776ef0db7b6ba2310785/master/w_828,c_limit/Portland-Maine-rose-1.jpg 2x" alt="Portland Maine rose 1" data-reactid="199"/></picture></div></div><figcaption class="callout-image-caption clearfix" data-reactid="200"><div class="credits" data-reactid="201">Elizabeth Cecil</div><span class="caption" data-reactid="202"><p>Rose Foods brings new meaning to &quot;power breakfast.&quot;</p>
</span></figcaption></figure><ol start="7" data-reactid="203"><li data-reactid="204"><p data-reactid="205"><!-- react-text: 206 -->Order the funky, fresh pho ga at <!-- /react-text --><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234/http://congtubot.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-reactid="207">Cong Tu Bot</a><!-- react-text: 208 --> on Portland’s restaurant row, Washington Avenue. Actually, everything I tried at Vien Dobui and Jessica Sheahan’s lively Vietnamese street food spot was brimming with herbs, heat, and soul.<!-- /react-text --></p></li><li data-reactid="209"><p data-reactid="210"><!-- react-text: 211 -->Try your best not to fill up on the standout small plates (see: house-made morcilla, cured local bluefish on smoked onions) at Spanish-leaning <!-- /react-text --><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234/https://www.chavalmaine.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-reactid="212">Chaval</a><!-- react-text: 213 -->, or you’ll risk being too full to try Ilma Lopez’s desserts. She’s one of the most talented pastry chefs in town, just as skilled with the simple (sticky and addictive maple pie) as the ornate (Paris-Brest with cacao sorbet).<!-- /react-text --></p></li><li data-reactid="214"><p data-reactid="215"><!-- react-text: 216 -->Swing by <!-- /react-text --><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234/https://www.littlegiantmaine.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-reactid="217">Little Giant</a><!-- react-text: 218 -->, the sophomore effort from the team behind local favorite <!-- /react-text --><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234/https://www.huntandalpineclub.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-reactid="219">Portland Hunt + Alpine Club</a><!-- react-text: 220 -->, which gets clever with dishes like lobster chips with serrano ranch and Moxie-braised pork belly. The sister market next door sells local beers and groceries and daily specials (don’t miss Friday and Saturday’s roast chicken and biscuits).<!-- /react-text --></p></li></ol><figure class="embedded-image embedded-image--no-callout" data-type="image" data-reactid="221"><div class="image-content" data-reactid="222"><div class="component-rendition ba-picture size_w414 size_h0 sm_w768 sm_h0 md_w1024 md_h0 lg_w1440 lg_h0 xl_w2000 xl_h0 xs_w414 xs_h0" data-component="Rendition" style="background-image:url(https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b699b698251ae0b4b651d97/master/w_10,c_limit/BA090118portland06.png);background-size:cover;background-repeat:no-repeat;" data-reactid="223"><picture data-reactid="224"><source srcset="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b699b698251ae0b4b651d97/master/w_2000/BA090118portland06.png 1x, https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b699b698251ae0b4b651d97/master/w_4000/BA090118portland06.png 2x" media="(min-width: 1488px)" data-reactid="225"/><source srcset="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b699b698251ae0b4b651d97/master/w_1440/BA090118portland06.png 1x, https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b699b698251ae0b4b651d97/master/w_2880/BA090118portland06.png 2x" media="(min-width: 1280px)" data-reactid="226"/><source srcset="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b699b698251ae0b4b651d97/master/w_1024/BA090118portland06.png 1x, https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b699b698251ae0b4b651d97/master/w_2048/BA090118portland06.png 2x" media="(min-width: 1024px)" data-reactid="227"/><source srcset="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b699b698251ae0b4b651d97/master/w_768/BA090118portland06.png 1x, https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b699b698251ae0b4b651d97/master/w_1536/BA090118portland06.png 2x" media="(min-width: 768px)" data-reactid="228"/><source srcset="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b699b698251ae0b4b651d97/master/w_414,c_limit/BA090118portland06.png 1x, https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b699b698251ae0b4b651d97/master/w_828,c_limit/BA090118portland06.png 2x" media="(min-width: 0px)" data-reactid="229"/><img class="ba-picture--fit" srcset="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b699b698251ae0b4b651d97/master/w_414,c_limit/BA090118portland06.png 1x, https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b699b698251ae0b4b651d97/master/w_828,c_limit/BA090118portland06.png 2x" alt="Portland-Cong-Tu-Bot-2.png" data-reactid="230"/></picture></div></div><figcaption class="callout-image-caption clearfix" data-reactid="231"><div class="credits" data-reactid="232">Elizabeth Cecil</div><span class="caption" data-reactid="233"><p>You need these turmeric-and-lemongrass-laced curry noodles at Cong Tu Bot.</p>
</span></figcaption></figure><ol start="10" data-reactid="234"><li data-reactid="235"><p data-reactid="236"><!-- react-text: 237 -->Visit the wine bar of my dreams: <!-- /react-text --><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234/http://www.drifterswife.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-reactid="238">Drifters Wife</a><!-- react-text: 239 --> (another <!-- /react-text --><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234/https://www.bonappetit.com/story/top-50-best-new-restaurants-2018" data-reactid="240">Top 50</a><!-- react-text: 241 --> nominee!). Basically, I want the life of owners Peter and Orenda Hale. They’re constantly popping open bottles of chuggable <!-- /react-text --><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234/https://www.bonappetit.com/story/what-is-natural-wine" data-reactid="242">natural wines</a><!-- react-text: 243 --> from their wine shop and then skipping over to the dining room to feast on mussel toast with nduja and other seasonal plates from chef Ben Jackson. At least this is how I want to believe they live.<!-- /react-text --></p></li><li data-reactid="244"><p data-reactid="245"><!-- react-text: 246 -->Follow <!-- /react-text --><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234/https://www.facebook.com/mr.tunamaine/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-reactid="247">Mr. Tuna</a><!-- react-text: 248 --> (a.k.a. Jordan Rubin) and his Japanese-style temaki hand rolls to whatever location he’s popping up at that day. Equipped with only a rice warmer, two Yeti coolers packed with his <!-- /react-text --><em data-reactid="249">mise en place</em><!-- react-text: 250 -->, and a cutting board, Rubin frequents breweries and special events serving impeccably fresh seafood. The spicy scallops and crab roll is a bar snack par excellence, but it’s the crab with yuzu mayo and avocado that convinced me to buy a Mr. Tuna T-shirt. I’ve got no problem being a walking advertisement for the guy.<!-- /react-text --></p></li><li data-reactid="251"><p data-reactid="252"><!-- react-text: 253 -->Learn why beer geeks get giddy about Portland. Every single day a new brewery opens somewhere in Maine. I’m kidding, kinda. My favorites (with tasting rooms, of course) include groundbreaking <!-- /react-text --><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234/https://www.allagash.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-reactid="254">Allagash</a><!-- react-text: 255 -->, <!-- /react-text --><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234/https://www.bissellbrothers.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-reactid="256">Bissell Brothers</a><!-- react-text: 257 -->, <!-- /react-text --><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234/https://oxbowbeer.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-reactid="258">Oxbow</a><!-- react-text: 259 -->, and <!-- /react-text --><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234/http://foundationbrew.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-reactid="260">Foundation</a><!-- react-text: 261 -->, but newcomer <!-- /react-text --><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234/http://www.austinstreetbrewery.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-reactid="262">Austin Street Brewery</a><!-- react-text: 263 --> is getting the buzz of late.<!-- /react-text --></p></li><li data-reactid="264"><p data-reactid="265"><!-- react-text: 266 -->Explore the <!-- /react-text --><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234/https://www.publicmarkethouse.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-reactid="267">Public Market House</a><!-- react-text: 268 -->—part mall food court, part restaurant incubator. The gem of the bi-level space is <!-- /react-text --><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234/https://www.maizportland.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-reactid="269">Maiz</a><!-- react-text: 270 -->, which serves arepas sliced open like a pita and stuffed with ingredients like chorizo, avocado, and zingy chimichurri sauce.<!-- /react-text --></p></li></ol><figure class="embedded-image embedded-image--no-callout" data-type="image" data-reactid="271"><div class="image-content" data-reactid="272"><div class="component-rendition ba-picture size_w414 size_h0 sm_w768 sm_h0 md_w1024 md_h0 lg_w1440 lg_h0 xl_w2000 xl_h0 xs_w414 xs_h0" data-component="Rendition" style="background-image:url(https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64670f0179fe6911740e51/master/w_10,c_limit/portland-maine-mr-tuna-1.jpg);background-size:cover;background-repeat:no-repeat;" data-reactid="273"><picture data-reactid="274"><source srcset="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64670f0179fe6911740e51/master/w_2000/portland-maine-mr-tuna-1.jpg 1x, https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64670f0179fe6911740e51/master/w_4000/portland-maine-mr-tuna-1.jpg 2x" media="(min-width: 1488px)" data-reactid="275"/><source srcset="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64670f0179fe6911740e51/master/w_1440/portland-maine-mr-tuna-1.jpg 1x, https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64670f0179fe6911740e51/master/w_2880/portland-maine-mr-tuna-1.jpg 2x" media="(min-width: 1280px)" data-reactid="276"/><source srcset="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64670f0179fe6911740e51/master/w_1024/portland-maine-mr-tuna-1.jpg 1x, https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64670f0179fe6911740e51/master/w_2048/portland-maine-mr-tuna-1.jpg 2x" media="(min-width: 1024px)" data-reactid="277"/><source srcset="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64670f0179fe6911740e51/master/w_768/portland-maine-mr-tuna-1.jpg 1x, https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64670f0179fe6911740e51/master/w_1536/portland-maine-mr-tuna-1.jpg 2x" media="(min-width: 768px)" data-reactid="278"/><source srcset="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64670f0179fe6911740e51/master/w_414,c_limit/portland-maine-mr-tuna-1.jpg 1x, https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64670f0179fe6911740e51/master/w_828,c_limit/portland-maine-mr-tuna-1.jpg 2x" media="(min-width: 0px)" data-reactid="279"/><img class="ba-picture--fit" srcset="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64670f0179fe6911740e51/master/w_414,c_limit/portland-maine-mr-tuna-1.jpg 1x, https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64670f0179fe6911740e51/master/w_828,c_limit/portland-maine-mr-tuna-1.jpg 2x" alt="portland maine mr tuna 1" data-reactid="280"/></picture></div></div><figcaption class="callout-image-caption clearfix" data-reactid="281"><div class="credits" data-reactid="282">Elizabeth Cecil</div><span class="caption" data-reactid="283"><p>Mr. Tuna on the job at Goodfire Brewing Co.</p>
</span></figcaption></figure><ol start="14" data-reactid="284"><li data-reactid="285"><p data-reactid="286"><!-- react-text: 287 -->Don’t skip the city’s trailblazers. When I was in college in nearby Lewiston a couple decades ago, a big night out with the visiting parents meant dinner at <!-- /react-text --><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234/http://www.forestreet.biz/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-reactid="288">Fore Street</a><!-- react-text: 289 -->, which is still going strong. Add the reinvented <!-- /react-text --><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234/http://www.hugos.net/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-reactid="290">Hugo’s</a><!-- react-text: 291 --> and the locals’ beloved <!-- /react-text --><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234/https://backbaygrill.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-reactid="292">Back Bay Grill</a><!-- react-text: 293 --> to the classics list.<!-- /react-text --></p></li><li data-reactid="294"><p data-reactid="295"><!-- react-text: 296 -->Ask yourself: What is <!-- /react-text --><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234/https://tentenpieportland.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-reactid="297">Ten Ten Pié</a><!-- react-text: 298 -->? A French bakery? Japanese market? Bento box cafe? It doesn’t matter—I’m a fan of baker Atsuko Fujimoto (that rhubarb tart!) and Markos Miller’s eclectic general store, whatever it is.<!-- /react-text --></p></li><li data-reactid="299"><p data-reactid="300"><!-- react-text: 301 -->Leave town! Biddeford is the best reason to drive 18 miles south. It’s home to one of the country’s best cookbook stores, <!-- /react-text --><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234/https://www.rabelaisbooks.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-reactid="302">Rabelais</a><!-- react-text: 303 --> (say hello to Don and Sam for me) and upstarts <!-- /react-text --><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234/https://www.instagram.com/littlesprucebakingco/?hl=en" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-reactid="304">Little Spruce Baking Co.</a><!-- react-text: 305 --> and <!-- /react-text --><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234/https://www.eldamaine.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-reactid="306">Elda</a><!-- react-text: 307 --> restaurant. It’s also home to the Single. Best. Diner. On. The. Planet. <!-- /react-text --><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234/http://www.palacedinerme.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-reactid="308">Palace Diner</a><!-- react-text: 309 -->. The flapjacks are towering, the burger is smashed and crunchy, and the tuna salad sandwich is quickly becoming a Maine icon.<!-- /react-text --></p></li></ol><figure class="embedded-image embedded-image--no-callout" data-type="image" data-reactid="310"><div class="image-content" data-reactid="311"><div class="component-rendition ba-picture size_w414 size_h0 sm_w768 sm_h0 md_w1024 md_h0 lg_w1440 lg_h0 xl_w2000 xl_h0 xs_w414 xs_h0" data-component="Rendition" style="background-image:url(https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64672c7e2a9576a88d599c/master/w_10,c_limit/Portland-Maine-Belleville.jpg);background-size:cover;background-repeat:no-repeat;" data-reactid="312"><picture data-reactid="313"><source srcset="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64672c7e2a9576a88d599c/master/w_2000/Portland-Maine-Belleville.jpg 1x, https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64672c7e2a9576a88d599c/master/w_4000/Portland-Maine-Belleville.jpg 2x" media="(min-width: 1488px)" data-reactid="314"/><source srcset="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64672c7e2a9576a88d599c/master/w_1440/Portland-Maine-Belleville.jpg 1x, https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64672c7e2a9576a88d599c/master/w_2880/Portland-Maine-Belleville.jpg 2x" media="(min-width: 1280px)" data-reactid="315"/><source srcset="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64672c7e2a9576a88d599c/master/w_1024/Portland-Maine-Belleville.jpg 1x, https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64672c7e2a9576a88d599c/master/w_2048/Portland-Maine-Belleville.jpg 2x" media="(min-width: 1024px)" data-reactid="316"/><source srcset="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64672c7e2a9576a88d599c/master/w_768/Portland-Maine-Belleville.jpg 1x, https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64672c7e2a9576a88d599c/master/w_1536/Portland-Maine-Belleville.jpg 2x" media="(min-width: 768px)" data-reactid="317"/><source srcset="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64672c7e2a9576a88d599c/master/w_414,c_limit/Portland-Maine-Belleville.jpg 1x, https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64672c7e2a9576a88d599c/master/w_828,c_limit/Portland-Maine-Belleville.jpg 2x" media="(min-width: 0px)" data-reactid="318"/><img class="ba-picture--fit" srcset="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64672c7e2a9576a88d599c/master/w_414,c_limit/Portland-Maine-Belleville.jpg 1x, https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234im_/https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5b64672c7e2a9576a88d599c/master/w_828,c_limit/Portland-Maine-Belleville.jpg 2x" alt="Portland Maine Belleville" data-reactid="319"/></picture></div></div><figcaption class="callout-image-caption clearfix" data-reactid="320"><div class="credits" data-reactid="321">Elizabeth Cecil</div><span class="caption" data-reactid="322"><p>All the pastries at Belleville</p>
</span></figcaption></figure><ol start="17" data-reactid="323"><li data-reactid="324"><p data-reactid="325"><!-- react-text: 326 -->Carbo-load at <!-- /react-text --><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234/https://blvl.me/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-reactid="327">Belleville</a><!-- react-text: 328 -->, which is putting out the city’s best and butteriest croissants. Arrive at 11:30 a.m. sharp—that’s when the shop’s other signature dish, <!-- /react-text --><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234/https://www.bonappetit.com/story/regional-pizza-styles" data-reactid="329">Roman-style pizza al taglio</a><!-- react-text: 330 -->, is pulled from the oven with toppings like fig and rosemary or shiitake and Gruyère. They also play Rush!<!-- /react-text --></p></li><li data-reactid="331"><p data-reactid="332"><!-- react-text: 333 -->Discover my perfect hangout. Thanks to a tip from Kazeem Lawal of <!-- /react-text --><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234/https://www.portlandtradingco.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-reactid="334">Portland Trading Co.</a><!-- react-text: 335 --> (he plays the best vinyl) just up the street, I found out about a tiny pub called <!-- /react-text --><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234/https://www.facebook.com/portlandmaine.MAPS/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-reactid="336">Maps</a><!-- react-text: 337 --> with local craft beers, vinyl, and vintage, yes, maps. When lobster-roll-seeking tourists of the Old Port are too much, this is your safe place.<!-- /react-text --></p></li><li data-reactid="338"><p data-reactid="339"><!-- react-text: 340 -->Make room for Middle Eastern–inspired <!-- /react-text --><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234/https://www.baharatmaine.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-reactid="341">Baharat</a><!-- react-text: 342 -->’s Turkish crab dip with house-made chips and takoyaki and okonomiyaki from Japanese comfort food spot <!-- /react-text --><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234/https://mamifoodtruck.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-reactid="343">Mami</a><!-- react-text: 344 -->, which prove that you can go from great food truck to even better brick-and-mortar.<!-- /react-text --></p></li><li data-reactid="345"><p data-reactid="346"><!-- react-text: 347 -->Pull up a stool at tried-and-true <!-- /react-text --><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234/http://www.dimillos.com/restaurant/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-reactid="348">DiMillo’s on the Water</a><!-- react-text: 349 --> for the old-school wood bar, prime people-watching, and bacon-wrapped scallops.<!-- /react-text --></p></li></ol><p data-reactid="350"><em data-reactid="351">Check back Tuesday, August 14, to find out if Rose Foods or Drifters Wife made the Hot 10.</em></p></div></div><div class="col col-xs-4 col-sm-12 col-md-4 col--MainWithSidebar col--secondary" data-component="Col" data-reactid="352"><div data-reactid="353"><div class="component-stickybox component-stickybox-ba" data-component="Stickybox" style="height:auto;" data-reactid="354"><div class="inner" style="width:auto;" data-reactid="355"><div class="sticky-video-target" data-reactid="356"></div><div class="cns--box_top" data-reactid="357"></div><div class="secondary-content " data-reactid="358"><!-- react-empty: 359 --></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="row" data-component="Row" data-reactid="360"><div class="col " data-component="Col" data-reactid="361"><div class="outbrain-section" data-reactid="362"><div class="component-outbrain" data-reactid="363"><div class="OUTBRAIN outbrain-content" data-src="https://web.archive.org/web/20180920201234oe_/https://www.bonappetit.com/story/portland-maine-city-of-the-year-2018" data-widget-id="AR_4" data-ob-template="Bonappetit" data-reactid="364"></div></div></div></div></div><div class="row row-